                            <comment id="14480715" author="paulk" created="Fri, 22 Aug 2014 19:26:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is supposed to appear within the h2 tag but it assumes (too simply) that the content won&apos;t have illegal characters, e.g. it expects something like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;h2 title=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Classes &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; the JMX Builder.&quot;&lt;/span&gt; class=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;title&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;Classes &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; the JMX Builder.&amp;lt;/h2&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The title attribute is filled in for accessibility reasons.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should really encode any quotes and strip or encode any tags within the &quot;title&quot; attribute value.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14480800" author="paulk" created="Fri, 13 Mar 2015 06:13:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I changed the template to have a standard title attribute and moved the H2 element after the title - as per what you were expecting and indeed how it is produced in recent versions of javadoc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
